    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Jackets that formed part of the military costume of the hussars, between hip and knee length. The jackets were decorated with five rows of braid frogging, looped into rosettes at the ends, with toggle closures incorporated into the frogging. Matching piping adorned the collar, front edge, bottom hem, back seams, and rear skirts.</Note_Text>
